The paper deals with a pattern matching problem in strings, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of fingerprint computation and sliding window approach suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem also involves counting and combinatorics, which are relevant to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The experimental evaluation of the algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG), as these fields often involve empirical evaluation of algorithms.
